  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Oral estrogens may be an effective adjuvant treatment for control of acromegaly in patients
      with resistance to somatostatin analogs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This will be a canadian multicenter study with a randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled
      design, to assess the efficacy and safety of adjuvant alesse in female acromegalic patients
      with suboptimal response to sandostatin LAR treatment.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
